         <abstract>
            <p>A polynomial representation for the second-derivative linear multistep methods for solving ordinary differential equations is presented. This representation leads to an implementation of the second-derivative methods using the Nordsieck polynomial representation. Possible advantages of such an implementation are then discussed.</p>
